  "text": "Language modeling is key to many problems such as speech recognition, machine translation or image captioning. RNNs and LSTMs have both been used to map sequences to sequences as well. Sequence to sequence models are made up of two RNNs; an encoder to process the input and a decoder to generate the output. In [CITATION_1] , multi-layered RNN cells have been used for the translation tasks and were evaluated on a popular English to French translation from the WMT'14 data set [CITATION_2] .",
